  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (44f26a8 2022-05-25T00:04:15.359167797Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge fmt\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nLinux\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nRunning `forge fmt` deletes all of my inline comments. I love the formatter (especially the `--check` output), but can't use it in write mode currently because of this issue. This may be tracked somewhere already, but couldn't find it\r\n\r\nexample `forge fmt --check` output showing the intention to delete inline comment\r\n```\r\n855 848  |     }\r\n856 849  | \r\n857 850  |     function testXYZ(uint128 seed, uint8 count) public {\r\n858      |-        // note lorem ipsum\r\n860 852  |         uint256[] memory tokenIds = new uint256[](count);\r\n861 853  |         uint256[] memory amounts = new uint256[](count);\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n```",
